## purpose
Defines security controls for 1000480006 ORGANIZATION VALIDATION SECURITY.

## security_objectives
- protect identity scope
- protect role scope
- protect boundary scope
- protect masked outputs
- prevent privilege widening through shortcuts

## trust_boundary
This subject must distinguish
owner,
operator,
reviewer,
approver,
and adapter trust positions.

## access_rules
- identity entitlement must be known
- role entitlement must be known
- boundary scope must be allowed
- output scope must be bounded
- masked outputs must remain masked

## masking_rules
When masking is required,
output must remain clearly bounded
and must not resemble full-authority output.

## audit_rules
Security-relevant actions
must remain auditable without exposing
more data than required.

## failure_codes
- SUBJECT_SEC_IDENTITY_DENIED
- SUBJECT_SEC_ROLE_DENIED
- SUBJECT_SEC_BOUNDARY_DENIED
- SUBJECT_SEC_SCOPE_DENIED
- SUBJECT_SEC_MASK_REQUIRED

## review_checklist
- trust boundary is explicit
- access rules are explicit
- masking rules are explicit
- audit rules are explicit
- denial behavior is explicit
